article.headline: Fairfield 67, Hawaii 65
article.story:
HONOLULU (AP) -- Emily Christian had 18 points and eight rebounds
to lead Tennessee Tech to a 64-59 victory over Hawaii on Tuesday in
the consolation game of the Ala Moana Hotel Paradise Classic.

Jenna Baltimore added 15 points and seven rebounds for the
Golden Eaglettes (3-5). Casey Bradford had 10 points.

Jade Abele led the Rainbow Wahine with 20 points; Bryony Crouch
added another 10 for Hawaii (2-7).

Hawaii's consolation game loss came after the team fell to
Fairfield 67-65 on Monday. Tennessee Tech's win in the Paradise
Classic came after losing 76-73 to Northern Iowa on Monday.

The Golden Eaglettes led 26-18 at the half and went 14-of-18
from the foul line.
